"{\"uid\": \"wired.com-story-jesse-grupper-gear-olympics-2024\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"In the pastfew years, sport climbing has become one of the fastest-growing sports in the world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 95, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pastfew years\", \"from\": 3, \"to\": 20}, {\"ngram\": \"sport climbing\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 36}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest-growing sports\", \"from\": 55, \"to\": 81}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 85, \"to\": 94}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This explosion in popularity could be because of superstars like Alex Honnold, who in addition to starring in the documentaryFree Solonow has several climbing shows withNational Geographic.\", \"from\": 97, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 162, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alex Honnold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Honnold\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This explosion\", \"from\": 97, \"to\": 111}, {\"ngram\": \"popularity\", \"from\": 115, \"to\": 125}, {\"ngram\": \"superstars\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 156}, {\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 191}, {\"ngram\": \"the documentaryFree\", \"from\": 207, \"to\": 226}, {\"ngram\": \"Solonow\", \"from\": 227, \"to\": 234}, {\"ngram\": \"several climbing\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 255}, {\"ngram\": \"withNational Geographic\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 285}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It could also be the proliferation of easily accessible indoor gyms.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the proliferation\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 321}, {\"ngram\": \"easily accessible indoor gyms\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Or maybe it's just because sport climbing is the safer way to go up a wall; its competitors clip ropes into secure, pre-drilled bolts rather than setting their own protective equipment the way traditional, or trad, climbers do.\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sport climbing\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 397}, {\"ngram\": \"the safer way\", \"from\": 401, \"to\": 414}, {\"ngram\": \"a wall\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 430}, {\"ngram\": \"its competitors\", \"from\": 432, \"to\": 447}, {\"ngram\": \"ropes\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"secure, pre-drilled bolts\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 489}, {\"ngram\": \"their own protective equipment\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"climbers\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The sport made its Olympic debut at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, with climbers matching up in three different formats: speed, lead, and bouldering.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The sport\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 594}, {\"ngram\": \"its Olympic debut\", \"from\": 600, \"to\": 617}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2020 Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"climbers\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"three different formats\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"lead\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 711}, {\"ngram\": \"bouldering\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"US climber Nathaniel Coleman secured a gold medal in the men's combined event at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"score\": 0.999997474531034, \"rank\": 2.5254726805304766e-06, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_dollar\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\", \"score\": 0.9999991758226073, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nathaniel Coleman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nathaniel_Coleman\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 778}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's combined event\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Games\", \"from\": 810, \"to\": 825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This August, American Jesse Grupper will be competing in Paris.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999977808754077, \"rank\": 2.2191214266790833e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 885, \"end\": 890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6901796978314001e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Grupper is from Montclair, New Jersey, where he started climbing in an indoor gym when he was six.\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 0.9999999936253516, \"rank\": 6.370862659315888e-09, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Grupper\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 899}, {\"ngram\": \"Montclair\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"an indoor gym\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He earned his degree in mechanical engineering from Tufts and worked inHarvard's Biodesign Lab, developing exoskeletons for stroke victims, and he is currently still a research fellow in the lab.\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1186, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his degree\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1011}, {\"ngram\": \"mechanical engineering\", \"from\": 1015, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"Tufts\", \"from\": 1043, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"inHarvard's Biodesign Lab\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1085}, {\"ngram\": \"developing exoskeletons\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"stroke victims\", \"from\": 1115, \"to\": 1129}, {\"ngram\": \"a research fellow\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"the lab\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1185}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Grupper largely pivoted away from the academic research life when he went full-time pro and started cleaning up on the World Cup competition circuit.\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Grupper\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"the academic research life\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1252}, {\"ngram\": \"full-time pro\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1279}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Cup competition circuit\", \"from\": 1307, \"to\": 1340}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2023, he qualified for the 2024 Paris Olympics when he took gold in the men's combined lead and bouldering in Santiago at the2023 Pan American Games.\", \"from\": 1342, \"to\": 1494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"score\": 0.9999999980809662, \"rank\": 1.7761196082816948e-09, \"text\": \"Santiago\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Santiago\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's combined lead\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"Pan American Games\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1493}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I caught up with Jesse over Zoom on a sunny trainin